1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:02,586
<i>Previously
on Desperate Housewives...</i>

2
00:00:03,005 --> 00:00:04,880
<i>A mother protected her son.</i>

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:07,132
Here in America,
we actually get divorced

4
00:00:07,382 --> 00:00:10,405
- before we get married again.
- I will explain it all away.

5
00:00:10,922 --> 00:00:13,513
Your father told me
you called off the wedding.

6
00:00:14,806 --> 00:00:17,091
<i>Evil came to Wisteria lane.</i>

7
00:00:18,017 --> 00:00:19,929
- Susan, how is she?
- We don't know yet.

8
00:00:20,096 --> 00:00:22,946
- Nobody's talking to us.
- <i>It struck again...</i>

9
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:25,567
- Can't believe she's dead.
- I didn't know her

10
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:27,569
but I guess we're
sorta connected now.

11
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:30,113
- You would've liked her.
- <i>And fear set in.</i>

12
00:00:30,363 --> 00:00:32,240
Whoever attacked Julie
is still out there.

13
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:35,090
There is obviously a
madman on the loose.

14
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:37,329
<i>The stage was set...</i>

15
00:00:39,045 --> 00:00:41,249
I'm a little out of your league,
don't you think?

16
00:00:41,718 --> 00:00:43,068
<i>For the killer...</i>

17
00:00:43,844 --> 00:00:45,045
What are you doing?

18
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:46,755
<i>To strike again.</i>

19
00:00:53,479 --> 00:00:56,371
<i>There is a house
in the town of Fairview.</i>

20
00:00:56,980 --> 00:01:00,098
<i>Inside this house lives a monster...</i>

21
00:01:00,456 --> 00:01:03,331
<i>The kind who kills young women.</i>

22
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:08,909
<i>You may ask how such
a monster came to be,</i>

23
00:01:09,952 --> 00:01:13,587
<i>and that's a very
good question, indeed.</i>

24
00:01:15,977 --> 00:01:17,283
I'm out of scotch.

25
00:01:18,851 --> 00:01:20,897
I'll buy you some more
while I'm out.

26
00:01:21,064 --> 00:01:22,814
You got any in your room?

27
00:01:23,703 --> 00:01:25,503
No. And stay out of there.

28
00:01:26,259 --> 00:01:28,333
I know you've been
stealing my booze.

29
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:31,200
Stop being so paranoid.
I don't even drink.

30
00:01:31,881 --> 00:01:35,231
- Sure you don't.
- I gotta help Mrs. Scavo fix her car.

31
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:39,486
You can wait a little while, right?

32
00:01:48,153 --> 00:01:50,289
<i>His name was Eddie.</i>

33
00:01:53,129 --> 00:01:55,627
<i>Everyone thought he was harmless...</i>

34
00:01:58,987 --> 00:02:02,497
<i>Until the day his mother
went into his room.</i>

35
00:02:05,521 --> 00:02:08,891
<i>She was just looking
for a bottle of scotch...</i>

36
00:02:13,465 --> 00:02:16,479
<i>But found the truth instead.</i>

37
00:02:21,011 --> 00:02:24,500
<i>Soon everyone
in town would be asking,</i>

38
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:27,230
<i>"How could such a monster
come to be?"</i>

39
00:02:30,279 --> 00:02:32,919
<i>Sadly, the answer...</i>

40
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:36,302
<i>Would satisfy no one.</i>

