43
00:02:48,589 --> 00:02:50,776
<i>I met Eddie on a Monday.</i>

44
00:02:53,988 --> 00:02:55,925
<i>He had just turned 4.</i>

45
00:02:59,299 --> 00:03:01,911
If you're smart,
you'll take up jogging now.

46
00:03:02,078 --> 00:03:04,142
Don't wait till you're my age.
It's too late.

47
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:07,587
- <i>I can't do anything!</i>
- <i>At this point I'd settle for anything.</i>

48
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:10,223
<i>Do the dishes. Wipe down the counter.
You've given up!</i>

49
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:12,734
- <i>I'm doing the best I can.</i>
- What's going on in there?

50
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:15,618
<i>You know what?
I don't need this crap. I am done!</i>

51
00:03:15,785 --> 00:03:17,319
Baby, I said I was sorry!

52
00:03:17,486 --> 00:03:20,033
- Too late. I can't take it anymore.
- But you can't walk out.

53
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:22,557
- We have a kid!
- No, you have a kid.

54
00:03:22,724 --> 00:03:25,246
I never wanted him.
I never wanted any of this!

55
00:03:25,998 --> 00:03:26,998
Excuse me!

56
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:30,919
- Is this your child?
- What's it to you?

57
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:34,919
I'm sure you don't want to be
talking like this in front of him.

58
00:03:40,153 --> 00:03:42,597
- I was just leaving.
- Hank, don't do this!

59
00:03:43,055 --> 00:03:44,557
Don't leave me here.

60
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:46,557
I don't want to be alone.

61
00:03:59,365 --> 00:04:00,532
Eddie, come here.

62
00:04:01,392 --> 00:04:03,942
Come here,
I have to get ready for work.

63
00:04:11,016 --> 00:04:12,168
It's you.

64
00:04:13,788 --> 00:04:16,058
I just wanted to check in,

65
00:04:16,225 --> 00:04:18,075
see how you guys are doing.

66
00:04:19,005 --> 00:04:21,469
Also, I made you a little something.

67
00:04:21,983 --> 00:04:23,056
You're kidding.

68
00:04:23,223 --> 00:04:26,224
It's nothing special,
just macaroni and cheese.

69
00:04:29,359 --> 00:04:31,396
Come on. Let me heat
this up for you.

70
00:04:34,047 --> 00:04:36,188
- I don't know.
- And then we can talk.

71
00:04:36,355 --> 00:04:39,247
And if you want to complain
about your husband, I promise,

72
00:04:39,414 --> 00:04:40,822
I won't defend him.

73
00:04:42,570 --> 00:04:44,520
Don't just stand there, then.

74
00:04:45,229 --> 00:04:46,279
Come on in.

75
00:04:52,844 --> 00:04:54,636
He's a handsome little boy.

76
00:04:54,803 --> 00:04:56,753
Looks just like his father...

77
00:04:57,351 --> 00:04:58,548
which is a shame.

78
00:05:01,029 --> 00:05:02,552
Maybe Hank will reconsider.

79
00:05:03,769 --> 00:05:05,419
He's serious this time.

80
00:05:06,397 --> 00:05:08,600
I'm all alone
with a 4-year-old to raise.

81
00:05:09,196 --> 00:05:11,406
Isn't there anybody
who can help you?

82
00:05:11,573 --> 00:05:13,988
- Family, your mother?
- My mother.

83
00:05:14,645 --> 00:05:15,690
God forbid.

84
00:05:16,325 --> 00:05:17,735
What about friends?

85
00:05:17,902 --> 00:05:21,008
I have a great group of friends
over on Wisteria lane.

86
00:05:21,175 --> 00:05:24,120
We've helped each other
get through all sorts of problems.

87
00:05:25,072 --> 00:05:28,548
I've never really been the
type of woman to have girlfriends.

88
00:05:28,715 --> 00:05:29,715
And now

89
00:05:30,218 --> 00:05:32,112
I'm 35 years old with a kid.

90
00:05:32,279 --> 00:05:35,668
I'm guessing I'm not really going
to be having any boyfriends either.

91
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:39,796
Don't be ridiculous.
Women in your situation find love.

92
00:05:39,963 --> 00:05:41,424
You just have to look for it.

93
00:05:43,041 --> 00:05:45,136
- I guess.
- Well, I've gotta go.

94
00:05:48,397 --> 00:05:50,308
If you like,
I can stop by next week.

95
00:05:51,777 --> 00:05:53,753
You don't have to do that.
We'll be fine.

96
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,521
Eddie, say good-bye to Mary Alice.

97
00:05:56,575 --> 00:05:58,885
- Good-bye.
- You take care, Eddie.

98
00:05:59,832 --> 00:06:00,832
So cute.

99
00:06:02,058 --> 00:06:04,458
He's gonna be
a heartbreaker one day.

100
00:06:06,639 --> 00:06:08,526
Just like his father.

101
00:06:21,799 --> 00:06:22,861
Hi, Eddie.

102
00:06:23,635 --> 00:06:24,735
Remember me?

103
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,913
I brought you a little something.

104
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,765
I'm not supposed to open the door.

105
00:06:31,740 --> 00:06:33,768
Tell your mom I'm here,
and she can open it.

106
00:06:34,443 --> 00:06:35,728
She's not here.

107
00:06:36,889 --> 00:06:38,564
Well, tell your babysitter then.

108
00:06:42,290 --> 00:06:44,070
You do have a sitter, don't you?

109
00:06:47,294 --> 00:06:49,594
Eddie, where exactly is your mother?

110
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:02,222
Oh, my gosh!
What are you doing here?

111
00:07:02,937 --> 00:07:05,675
Look, it's my friend, Mary Alice.

112
00:07:06,109 --> 00:07:07,510
Nice to meet you, Mary.

113
00:07:07,934 --> 00:07:10,138
The name's Ron.
Can I buy you a drink?

114
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:13,308
Thanks, but I'm not gonna be here
that long. Get up. You're leaving.

115
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:17,854
She can't leave yet.
This party's just getting started.

116
00:07:18,457 --> 00:07:20,523
Did you say your name was Ron?

117
00:07:20,996 --> 00:07:23,318
Shut up, Ron.
I have Eddie in my car.

118
00:07:24,494 --> 00:07:26,821
Has something happened?
He's not hurt, is he?

119
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:29,407
- He's fine, no thanks to you.
- Who's Eddie?

120
00:07:29,657 --> 00:07:32,639
Her 4-year-old child
who she left at her home, unattended.

121
00:07:32,806 --> 00:07:34,006
You got a kid?

122
00:07:34,349 --> 00:07:36,432
You might wanna lead
with that next time,

123
00:07:36,599 --> 00:07:38,999
before I spring for
the screwdrivers.

124
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:43,546
Don't you wanna get my phone number?

125
00:07:44,876 --> 00:07:46,424
Look at what you've done.

126
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:48,977
I am this close
to calling social services.

127
00:07:49,144 --> 00:07:51,000
You might wanna change your tone.

128
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:54,117
Let's go.
You've got a little boy to look after.

129
00:07:57,658 --> 00:07:59,625
I know I should have stayed home.

130
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:02,096
But I was already dressed
when the sitter canceled,

131
00:08:02,263 --> 00:08:04,776
and I really just needed
a couple of hours to myself.

132
00:08:05,180 --> 00:08:06,611
He's 4 years old, Barbara.

133
00:08:07,268 --> 00:08:09,676
What if he had gotten sick?
What if he had hurt himself?

134
00:08:09,843 --> 00:08:11,824
I know.
It was really stupid.

135
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:14,031
You've got to promise me
you will never

136
00:08:14,198 --> 00:08:16,936
- do something like this again.
- Never again.

137
00:08:17,103 --> 00:08:18,103
I swear.

138
00:08:21,039 --> 00:08:22,139
It's just...

139
00:08:23,359 --> 00:08:24,359
What?

140
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,592
I really need a man.

141
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:36,018
My heavens. I should
have been home hours ago.

142
00:08:36,185 --> 00:08:38,559
Don't worry about us.
We are good now.

143
00:08:43,865 --> 00:08:46,315
I want you to be happy,
Barbara. I do.

144
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:48,569
It's just...

145
00:08:49,748 --> 00:08:51,161
Being a mother means

146
00:08:51,328 --> 00:08:53,533
always putting his needs
ahead of yours.

147
00:08:55,549 --> 00:08:56,699
You're right.

148
00:08:56,866 --> 00:08:58,816
That's exactly what it means.

149
00:09:07,008 --> 00:09:08,008
Come here.

150
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:17,137
It's not your fault
you ruined my life.

151
00:09:22,535 --> 00:09:25,189
<i>Gabrielle met Eddie on a Tuesday,</i>

152
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:27,859
<i>The day she moved
into the neighborhood.</i>

153
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:30,335
Carlos, I'm bored.

154
00:09:31,049 --> 00:09:34,476
I can't go get my nails done, because
I'm waiting for the freaking movers!

155
00:09:34,643 --> 00:09:37,181
Besides, I doubt this town
even has a SPA.

156
00:09:37,348 --> 00:09:40,578
It does, have annoying people who come
to your house with welcome baskets

157
00:09:40,745 --> 00:09:43,395
and say things like,
"Hot enough for you?"

158
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,567
No! You are not
going into another meeting!

159
00:09:46,734 --> 00:09:49,954
Just because I moved here
for your job, doesn't mean you...

160
00:09:51,145 --> 00:09:53,266
Damn right we're
gonna talk about this tonight,

161
00:09:53,433 --> 00:09:55,633
and it will be hot enough for you.

162
00:10:01,693 --> 00:10:04,040
Looks like it's just
you and me, Chanel.

163
00:10:22,384 --> 00:10:23,934
Who the hell are you?

164
00:10:24,919 --> 00:10:27,246
- How did you get in here?
- Through the window.

165
00:10:27,413 --> 00:10:30,379
- How did you get in?
- With my key. I own this place.

166
00:10:30,629 --> 00:10:34,175
I've been playing here since the other
people moved. Can I still do that?

167
00:10:35,305 --> 00:10:36,928
Get out. Go home.

168
00:10:41,361 --> 00:10:43,476
Did you know
you're really beautiful?

169
00:10:51,521 --> 00:10:53,916
Okay,
maybe I was a little rude earlier.

170
00:10:54,083 --> 00:10:56,322
- What's your story? What do you do?
- I'm a kid.

171
00:10:57,594 --> 00:10:59,951
- Right. So why aren't you in school?
- It's summer.

172
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:03,870
Right. Well,
I don't really do the kid thing.

173
00:11:04,037 --> 00:11:05,331
So, where do you live?

174
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:07,331
A couple of streets over.

175
00:11:07,749 --> 00:11:09,085
The house with the weeds.

176
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:16,107
That's the moving van that
has a lot of boxes I have to unpack.

177
00:11:16,274 --> 00:11:17,974
You better hit the road.

178
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:21,847
Or I could stay here
and help you unpack.

179
00:11:26,578 --> 00:11:27,645
Follow me.

180
00:11:32,063 --> 00:11:33,359
You missed a spot.

181
00:11:34,488 --> 00:11:36,362
- Sorry.
- Don't apologize.

182
00:11:36,612 --> 00:11:40,032
You do good work. Maybe next time
you'll be ready to do a French tip.

183
00:11:40,444 --> 00:11:41,844
Should I get that?

184
00:11:43,685 --> 00:11:46,261
Keep your voice down.
It might be one of those Stepford wives

185
00:11:46,428 --> 00:11:48,564
with another "Welcome to
the neighborhood" cake.

186
00:11:48,731 --> 00:11:50,501
Does it look like I eat cake?

187
00:11:51,036 --> 00:11:52,685
Some of the neighbors are nice.

188
00:11:52,852 --> 00:11:55,589
That lady with the red hair
makes her own Halloween candy.

189
00:11:55,839 --> 00:11:58,052
The one whose parents
named her after cheese?

190
00:11:58,219 --> 00:12:01,191
No, thank you. I like my robots
a little more lifelike.

191
00:12:02,326 --> 00:12:05,599
Though she's not as bad as that blonde
chick who's always yelling at her kids.

192
00:12:05,849 --> 00:12:08,311
There are people on fire
who are not as loud as she is.

193
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,647
And then I thought,
maybe for a second,

194
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:14,547
that Susan Mayer lady and I
could friends.

195
00:12:14,714 --> 00:12:16,664
And then she started talking.

196
00:12:18,713 --> 00:12:20,323
Good. I think they're gone.

197
00:12:21,765 --> 00:12:23,615
Can we watch our shows now?

198
00:12:23,782 --> 00:12:26,477
Just as soon as you finish unpacking
those boxes in the kitchen.

199
00:12:26,644 --> 00:12:28,244
I did it this morning.

200
00:12:30,211 --> 00:12:32,404
If you can sew, I am locking you
in my basement,

201
00:12:32,571 --> 00:12:35,296
- and you are staying here forever.
- Cool!

202
00:12:35,697 --> 00:12:37,078
Eddie, I was kidding.

203
00:12:37,245 --> 00:12:39,592
You've been coming here
every day for a week.

204
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,509
Doesn't your mother mind?

205
00:12:41,676 --> 00:12:44,126
Are you sure?
Maybe I should call her.

206
00:12:44,835 --> 00:12:47,975
She has this new boyfriend,
and they like their alone time.

207
00:12:51,272 --> 00:12:53,606
Then why don't you
stay for dinner? I'll cook.

208
00:12:54,036 --> 00:12:56,181
- Great!
- Although, you are the one who

209
00:12:56,348 --> 00:12:59,049
unpacked the pots and pans, so,
I'd hate to mess up your system.

210
00:12:59,216 --> 00:13:01,266
I'll cook.
I can heat up soup.

211
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:04,200
More than I can do.

212
00:13:08,082 --> 00:13:11,141
Yao Lin, how sick are you, really?
If you can dial a phone,

213
00:13:11,308 --> 00:13:14,210
you can come in and do three loads
of laundry and wash some dishes.

214
00:13:16,778 --> 00:13:20,728
You know I can't understand when
you speak in your native gibberish!

215
00:13:26,232 --> 00:13:27,306
Surprise, babe.

216
00:13:28,649 --> 00:13:30,101
What are you doing home?

217
00:13:30,597 --> 00:13:33,897
I was at work and I started
thinking about my lonely...

218
00:13:34,502 --> 00:13:35,752
beautiful wife.

219
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,985
And that big beautiful bathtub
upstairs we haven't christened yet.

220
00:13:40,714 --> 00:13:41,714
You pig.

221
00:13:43,079 --> 00:13:46,053
So you're saying you don't
wanna take a bath with me?

222
00:13:47,128 --> 00:13:51,077
I guess the pans can wait until Yao Lin
recovers from her double pneumonia.

223
00:13:55,568 --> 00:13:57,958
All right.
We've done the tub.

224
00:13:58,262 --> 00:14:01,132
Maybe we should christen
the guest room next.

225
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:03,314
That sounds great,
but I need to get going.

226
00:14:03,481 --> 00:14:06,262
Wait a minute. You're going back
to work? This is a nooner?

227
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:08,858
I can't take the whole day off.
I already canceled

228
00:14:09,025 --> 00:14:11,934
- two meetings and a lunch for this.
- So how long do we have?

229
00:14:12,343 --> 00:14:13,436
Five more minutes.

230
00:14:14,394 --> 00:14:16,772
Don't just sit there.
Fondle something.

231
00:14:18,522 --> 00:14:20,734
What the hell? Who are you?

232
00:14:22,853 --> 00:14:25,698
- You know this kid?
- He lives in the neighborhood.

233
00:14:26,184 --> 00:14:28,951
I knocked. No one answered.
So I came through the window.

234
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:31,245
We're naked. Get out!

235
00:14:31,495 --> 00:14:33,581
She told me I could come over.
Who's this guy?

236
00:14:34,406 --> 00:14:36,709
He's my husband, Eddie! Get out!

237
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:42,409
This is how you've been
spending your days?

238
00:14:43,426 --> 00:14:46,776
- He's lonely. I'm lonely.
- There are women on this street

239
00:14:46,943 --> 00:14:49,096
- you can be friends with.
- They're all so weird.

240
00:14:49,849 --> 00:14:52,600
Your best friend is a 9-year-old boy.
