00:33:09,994 --> 00:33:13,449
<i>that Lynette was clued in
to the truth of Eddie's life.</i>

490
00:33:13,699 --> 00:33:16,244
Three words.
Third word. Third word.

491
00:33:18,124 --> 00:33:19,124
You. You.

492
00:33:19,503 --> 00:33:20,915
Pregnant. Bloated.

493
00:33:21,165 --> 00:33:22,375
Swollen. Huge.

494
00:33:23,650 --> 00:33:25,795
- Lady, Tom. I'm a lady.
- No talking.

495
00:33:26,045 --> 00:33:27,545
Better than hitting.

496
00:33:29,131 --> 00:33:30,383
<i>Du Barry was a lady.</i>

497
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:32,343
<i>Three times a lady.</i>

498
00:33:32,593 --> 00:33:34,304
- <i>Tramp and the Lady</i>?
- No. <i>My Fair Lady</i>!

499
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:35,844
Yes. Yes!

500
00:33:36,710 --> 00:33:38,516
<i>Tramp and the lady</i>. Really?

501
00:33:40,250 --> 00:33:42,264
Coming!
It's not easy

502
00:33:42,431 --> 00:33:45,234
when you're swollen,
bloated and huge.

503
00:33:47,122 --> 00:33:48,192
Where's my kid?

504
00:33:48,670 --> 00:33:51,112
Hey, Barbara. He's in here with us.
You want to come in?

505
00:33:51,770 --> 00:33:52,770
No.

506
00:33:56,248 --> 00:33:57,398
Get out here.

507
00:34:03,299 --> 00:34:05,953
- What are you doing here?
- Why didn't you answer your phone?

508
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:07,636
That was probably our fault.

509
00:34:07,803 --> 00:34:10,443
We were playing charades,
and you know how loud that can get.

510
00:34:10,610 --> 00:34:12,592
I guess my invitation
got lost in the mail.

511
00:34:13,718 --> 00:34:16,380
- You gotta come home.
- It's not even 8:00, mom.

512
00:34:16,547 --> 00:34:18,181
- I don't care.
- I'm having fun.

513
00:34:18,431 --> 00:34:20,933
You should have thought about that
before you hid my stuff.

514
00:34:21,183 --> 00:34:23,220
- I didn't hide it.
- Everything okay?

515
00:34:23,387 --> 00:34:25,501
- It's nothing.
- Yeah, he hides my booze.

516
00:34:25,668 --> 00:34:27,982
And then acts all ashamed
when I call him on it.

517
00:34:28,369 --> 00:34:30,860
I know you hid it,
you little bastard.

518
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,904
Mrs. Scavo, it's okay. It's okay.

519
00:34:33,154 --> 00:34:35,304
Mom, come on. I'll walk you home.

520
00:34:38,986 --> 00:34:41,412
I don't think you should talk
to your son that way.

521
00:34:43,670 --> 00:34:46,751
What do you care? Huh?
What is he, your pet project?

522
00:34:47,646 --> 00:34:50,025
You feed him a little dinner,
Lynette, and then you

523
00:34:50,192 --> 00:34:53,800
let him play your stupid games
so you can feel good about yourself?

524
00:34:57,030 --> 00:34:58,221
I got your number.

525
00:35:22,396 --> 00:35:23,796
I'm out of scotch.

526
00:35:25,163 --> 00:35:27,563
I'll buy you some more
while I'm out.

527
00:35:27,974 --> 00:35:29,252
Got any in your room?

528
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:31,440
No. And stay out of there.

529
00:35:38,143 --> 00:35:40,743
Hi, Mrs. Scavo.
I'm here to fix your car.

530
00:35:41,572 --> 00:35:44,309
You are so sweet
to remember this. Thank you.

531
00:35:44,476 --> 00:35:47,145
So...
how are things at home?

532
00:35:48,595 --> 00:35:51,190
Are the tools in the garage?
I should probably get started.

533
00:36:05,599 --> 00:36:08,499
- We got any cake left?
- I'm not sure.

534
00:36:10,370 --> 00:36:11,370
You okay?

535
00:36:11,914 --> 00:36:15,111
I don't know. I keep
thinking about last night.

536
00:36:15,569 --> 00:36:17,049
Yeah, me, too.

537
00:36:17,399 --> 00:36:18,799
And I'm just so...

538
00:36:21,700 --> 00:36:22,700
livid.

539
00:36:24,795 --> 00:36:27,185
That Barbara
is an infuriating woman.

540
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:30,637
I am livid at us...

541
00:36:31,025 --> 00:36:33,566
the way she talked to Eddie
and we did nothing.

542
00:36:33,816 --> 00:36:37,425
I know. But we can't force her
to be nice to her own kid.

543
00:36:37,903 --> 00:36:40,103
That's what everybody always says.

544
00:36:40,565 --> 00:36:42,742
But we all know the woman
is a drunken nightmare.

545
00:36:42,992 --> 00:36:45,848
We complain about her,
we gossip about her,

546
00:36:46,015 --> 00:36:49,055
and then we watch her
walk into that house,

547
00:36:49,756 --> 00:36:52,509
where we know
something bad is happening.

548
00:36:53,067 --> 00:36:54,212
But we do nothing.

549
00:36:57,093 --> 00:36:58,093
Well...

550
00:36:58,730 --> 00:37:01,552
I'm tired of being one of the people
who does nothing.

551
00:37:03,415 --> 00:37:07,058
Eddie is an adult now and
he can leave whenever he wants.

552
00:37:07,402 --> 00:37:10,019
He's probably so damaged,
he doesn't know how to leave.

553
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:16,192
Where are you going with this?

554
00:37:17,690 --> 00:37:19,695
Ma, I'm back from the store.

555
00:37:24,700 --> 00:37:25,993
What is that?

556
00:37:26,846 --> 00:37:28,120
Your scrapbook.

557
00:37:31,409 --> 00:37:33,209
I don't understand, Eddie.

558
00:37:33,969 --> 00:37:36,927
There are all these
newspaper articles in here,

559
00:37:37,094 --> 00:37:39,280
about girls in Fairview
who've been...

560
00:37:40,250 --> 00:37:41,884
strangled or murdered.

561
00:37:45,570 --> 00:37:47,473
Why would you collect this stuff?

562
00:37:51,333 --> 00:37:53,533
Don't just look down at your feet.

563
00:37:54,410 --> 00:37:56,610
You gotta tell me the truth, okay?

564
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:00,410
Did you have anything to do with...

565
00:38:00,701 --> 00:38:01,863
hurting those girls?

566
00:38:11,841 --> 00:38:14,125
How could you do
something like this? Oh, God.

567
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:17,140
I didn't raise you to...
to be like this.

568
00:38:20,839 --> 00:38:21,883
Didn't you?

569
00:38:24,490 --> 00:38:27,180
What is that supposed to mean?
This is my fault?

570
00:38:29,514 --> 00:38:30,664
You're upset.

571
00:38:32,101 --> 00:38:34,937
Why don't you sit back down
and have something to drink?

572
00:38:36,110 --> 00:38:38,373
You're gonna try
to blame this on me.

573
00:38:38,540 --> 00:38:39,540
No way.

574
00:38:40,298 --> 00:38:41,650
Screw you.

575
00:38:44,864 --> 00:38:47,123
- What are you doing?
- What do you think I'm doing,

576
00:38:47,290 --> 00:38:50,620
- you moron? I'm calling the police!
- Don't do that. Put that down.

577
00:38:50,870 --> 00:38:54,582
I always said the worst mistake I ever
made in my life was having you.

578
00:39:35,164 --> 00:39:37,525
- Perfect timing.
- Mrs. Scavo, what are you doing here?

579
00:39:37,692 --> 00:39:40,711
Are you okay?
Oh, my gosh, you're trembling and...

580
00:39:40,961 --> 00:39:44,006
- I'm just... I was on my way out.
- Then I'll make this quick.

581
00:39:44,900 --> 00:39:47,150
Tom and I have been talking, and...

582
00:39:47,734 --> 00:39:50,513
we would like it
if you would move in with us.

583
00:39:52,343 --> 00:39:56,143
I know it's a big change, but
you've gotta get out of here, Eddie.

584
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:58,354
This isn't a healthy situation.

585
00:40:02,433 --> 00:40:04,283
I guess it could be better.

586
00:40:12,493 --> 00:40:13,744
Is she passed out?

587
00:40:16,466 --> 00:40:20,371
This is what I'm talking about.
This is why you need to get out of here.

588
00:40:20,538 --> 00:40:22,138
I mean, look at her...

589
00:40:23,259 --> 00:40:24,338
dead drunk.

590
00:40:28,593 --> 00:40:30,293
I'll come live with you.

591
00:40:30,460 --> 00:40:33,503
Great. So just pack your bags
and come on over.

592
00:40:33,670 --> 00:40:35,016
I hope you like meat loaf.

593
00:40:36,725 --> 00:40:39,770
You want me to come in and help you,
or do you want me to come back later

594
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:42,643
- to talk to her?
- Believe me, Mrs. Scavo,

595
00:40:42,810 --> 00:40:44,560
she wouldn't hear a word.

596
00:40:55,198 --> 00:40:58,420
<i>There is a house
in the town of Fairview.</i>

597
00:41:00,004 --> 00:41:02,915
<i>Inside this house lives a monster...</i>

598
00:41:04,870 --> 00:41:07,377
<i>The kind who kills women.</i>

599
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,307
<i>You may wonder</i>

600
00:41:10,474 --> 00:41:13,387
<i>how a monster like that came to be.</i>

601
00:41:14,736 --> 00:41:16,781
<i>The answer is simple...</i>

602
00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:19,885
<i>Monsters are created...</i>

603
00:41:20,843 --> 00:41:23,173
<i>by other monsters.</i>

